headline: More Pain Ahead for Software Laggards? What the Charts Say About 3 Stocks.
summary: Salesforce  once a marquee name in enterprise software, has struggled to keep pace in 2025.  While most software names remain well above their early April lows,  Salesforce  is oddly retesting that level.  Figma  a recent software IPO, has seen a brutal start to public trading.
